    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Bedford County was formed in 1753 from Lunenburg County.  Part of Albemarle was added in 1754 and part of Lunenburg was added later.  
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Bedford County (Va.) Records, 1772-1800.  Consists of two judgments, Burton v. Haynes, ca. 1797; and Evans v. Frederick, ca. 1799; the estate account of Richard Dearen, 1772; and a petition and report, 1800, pertaining to a proposed road from Davies' Ferry Road at the upper end of Philip Burton's plantation to the county line.         
</p>
    </scopecontent>
